<HEADLINE> U.S. Prices for Services Soaring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Service businesses are raising
their prices across the United States because of a tight labor
market in the country, according to U.S. media reports Monday.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that prices for services from cable TV to
dry-cleaning and haircuts are rising 3 percent a year.
</P>
<P>
But the prices of U.S. goods are falling or holding steady.
Falling energy prices sent wholesale prices lower for a fourth
straight month in February, according to the latest report of the
U.S. Labor Department.
</P>
<P>
Intense global competition, sharpened by the Asian financial
crisis and the strong U.S. dollar, combined with recent
productivity gains almost ensure that prices on goods will
continue to fall.
</P>
<P>
Goods account for some 42 percent in the U.S. economy while
services' share is 58 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
