<HEADLINE> Foreign Leaders Greet Newly-Elected Chinese Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Many foreign leaders Monday sent
telegrams congratulating the Chinese leaders newly elected during
the ongoing Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) of China.
</P>
<P>
Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Worker's Party of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea
(DPRK), chairman of the National Defense Commission and Supreme
Commander of the Korean People's Army, and Vietnam President Tran
Duc Luong; Shahabuddin Ahmed, president of Bangladesh; Japanese
Emperor Akihito; Tuanku Ja'afar, supreme head of state of
Malaysia; Sheikh Hasina, prime minister of Bangladesh, and Ryutaro
