<HEADLINE> 376 Nominations for HK's Sub-sector Elections Received </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A total of 158 nominations for
Hong Kong's Election Committee sub-sector elections were received
by the Registration and Electoral Office Tuesday, bringing the
total number of nominations to 376.
</P>
<P>
The nomination period started on March 13 and was scheduled to
last up to March 20.
</P>
<P>
Among all the 35 sectors, the latest official figures showed,
the information technology sector has had 39 nominations, the
engineering 35, the agriculture and fisheries 34, the labor 32,
the Medical 26, the education 24 and the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference 23.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials responsible for the election
affairs, "people need time to complete the forms and they also
need time to find nominators."
</P>
<P>
The sub-sector elections, which should produce a total of 683
members of the Election Committee on April 2, is part of the
Legislative Council elections scheduled for May 24.
</P>
<P>
These 683 members, together with the ex-officio members
including Hong Kong deputies to the National People's Congress
and Provisional Legislative Council members, as well as the
religious sub-sector, will form an 800-strong Election Committee.
</P>
<P>
The first Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region shall be composed of 60 members, with 20
returned by geographical constituencies through direct elections,
10 by the Election Committee and 30 by functional constituencies.
</P>
</TEXT>
