<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 5.94 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday closed at 3791.17
points, showing a net gain of 5.94 points from the previous close
of 3785.23.
</P>
<P>
The national index rose by 3.1 points to 1638.36 from the last
close of 1635.26.
</P>
<P>
Pivotals recovered from their lows and posted modest gains on
the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday on short covering
and squaring up of positions on the last day of trading for the
current settlement at the national stock exchange.  
</P>
