<HEADLINE> Bank of China Loans $70 Million to Shanghai Iron Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China today loaned
70 million U.S. dollars to Shanghai No.1 Iron and Steel Corp.,
helping it with a new construction project.
</P>
<P>
The corporation plans to build a blast furnace with a working
volume of 2,500 cubic meters, which should greatly increase its
pig iron production.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to save the company 300 million yuan
annually, or about 36 million U.S. dollars, in production costs.
</P>
<P>
Bank of China's Shanghai branch and the corporation will
further strengthen cooperation in project development, financial
consultation and other services.
</P>
<P>
The corporation, a local industrial group, owns property valued
at 5.5 billion yuan. It produces more than 40 percent of
Shanghai's yearly iron output and is among Shanghai's 50 strongest
enterprises in terms of the volume of imports and exports.
</P>
</TEXT>
