<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE) 100-Index dropped 61.42 points on Tuesday to close at
1526.32 from Monday's closing index of 1587.74.
</P>
<P>
A total of 65.6 million shares were traded Tuesday against 31.5
million shares Monday.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here believed that the drop of the KSE 100-Index was
in reaction to a statement by Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif that his
government was thinking of renegotiating power tariffs agreed by
the previous government.
</P>
<P>
The analysts are of the view that Sharif's statement might have
a negative impact on foreign investment in the long run.
</P>
<P>
There are expectations that the stock market will continue its
slide on Wednesday since there is little buying.
</P>
<P>
"Everybody is a seller," said one dealer, who expected the KSE
100-Index to go down 10 more points before making some sort of
recovery.  
