<DOCNO> XIE19980317.0028 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WEU Capable of Resolving Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Western European Union (WEU)
has been showing its ability to deal with the new strategic
situation effectively, said WEU Secretary-General Jose Cutileiro
Tuesday during the 50th anniversary of the Brussels Treaty, the
founding document of WEU.
</P>
<P>
"WEU is showing that it can respond to various crises that put
European interests at risk, especially those events with which
their North American allies do not wish to become directly
involved." said Cutileiro.
</P>
<P>
The WEU launched its first concerted action during the
Iran-Iraq war via a minesweeping operation in the Strait of
Hormuz. It later coordinated the minesweeping and embargo
monitoring operations during the Gulf war.
</P>
<P>
Then the European body helped set up a unified Croat-Muslim
police force to support the European Union administration in the
Bosnian city of Mostar.
</P>
<P>
Hans van den Broek, European commissioner responsible for
external relations, said that although the EU-WEU cooperation is
developing, the WEU still needs to express its readiness to
respond to EU requests.
</P>
<P>
The commissioner cited as a missed opportunity the WEU's
failure to decide on a contingency action when civil unrest broke
out in Albania last year.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1955, the WEU now has 10 members which consist of
Belgium, France, Germany, Greece, Italy, Luxembourg, the
Netherlands, Portugal, Spain and Britain.
</P>
<P>
The WEU also has three associate members that include Iceland,
Norway and Turkey; five observers made up of Austria, Denmark,
Finland, Ireland and Sweden; 10 associate partners from Bulgaria,
the Czech Republic, Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Poland,
Romania, Slovakia and Slovenia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
