<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Takes Action Against Polluting Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Indian pollution control
authorities have taken legal actions against 1,008 of 2,138
polluting industries for discharging effluents into rivers and
lakes without requisite treatment.
</P>
<P>
Dileep Biswas, chairman of the State Pollution Control Boards
(SPCBS), said Tuesday that the polluting units were given notices
Last August to install requisite effluent treatment equipment by
November last year.
</P>
<P>
Those which failed to do so in time were given closure notices,
Biswas added.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, four regional pollution control
committees have been set up to supervise pollution control efforts
of the SPCBS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
