<HEADLINE> U.S. Grants Philippines Extra Sugar Quota </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The United States has granted the
Philippines an additional sugar quota allocation of 27,411 metric
tons, bringing the country's total sugar quota this year to
178,426 metric tons, the Philippine News Agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The total U.S. sugar allocation will fetch an estimated revenue
of 2.68 billion pesos (67 million U.S. dollars) for the
Philippines, which is one of the major sugar suppliers of the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The news agency said the U.S. government had earlier announced
a total increase of 200,000 metric tons in sugar imports from
quota countries this year.
</P>
<P>
With the additional allocation, the Philippines could bring in
412 million pesos (10.3 million dollars) more in export earnings.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
