<HEADLINE> Greenpeace Protests Against German Nuclear Waste Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- About 25 members of the environmental
organization Greenpeace Tuesday climbed the chimney tower of a
coal-fired power station in the southwestern German town of Walheim to
protest against the transportation of nuclear waste.
</P>
<P>
The organization said it would occupy the tower for several days.
</P>
<P>
Containers with used nuclear fuel elements are expected to be
loaded onto train from heavy-duty trucks in the town, and then carried
to Ahaus, near the German-Dutch border, on March 25.
</P>
<P>
Greenpeace said the nuclear waste came from power stations of
Neckarswestheim and the Bavarian nuclear plant of Gundremmingen.
</P>
</TEXT>
