<HEADLINE> Philippines, Spain Sign Defense Cooperation Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines and Spain have
signed a memorandum of understanding to strengthen the logistics
capabilities of their armed forces, the Philippine News Agency
reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Defense Secretary Fortunato Abat and Spanish
Ambassador to the Philippines Uelfin Colome signed the document on
behalf of the two governments, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Abat said that under the memorandum of understanding, ties will
be expanded between the Philippine and the Spanish armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will also encourage and facilitate direct
contacts and cooperation between agencies of the two armed forces
in the areas of supply, maintenance, transportation, services and
other spheres of the logistics sub-systems as maybe agreed upon.
</P>
<P>
A joint committee, co-chaired by the assistant secretary for
installations of the Philippine Department of National Defense and
the director general for armament and equipment of the Spanish
Ministry of Defense, is scheduled to meet once a year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
