<HEADLINE> HK Celebrity Donates to Qinghua University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A foundation stone was laid here
today for the expansion of the kindergarten at Qinghua University,
one of the most prestigious colleges in China.
</P>
<P>
The kindergarten is specially for enrolling children of the
university's teachers and other staff members.
</P>
<P>
The expansion project was launched with an investment of 13.5
million yuan (1.7 million U.S. dollars). The money will also be
used for constructing a teaching building. Wang Liangjihua, a Hong
Kong celebrity, donated 10 million Hong Kong dollars (1.3 million
U.S. dollars) for the projects.
</P>
<P>
Wang is the daughter of the late Liang Qiuju, a co-founder of
the Ho Leung Ho Lee (HLHL) Foundation, China's biggest
non-governmental award for scientific development.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who is known for her public welfare activities, also
joined her father and husband in donating 12 million Hong Kong
dollars for the construction of the architecture building of
Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
The teaching building will cover an area of more than 5,400
square meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
