<HEADLINE> Macao Gasoline Price Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The price for gasoline products
dropped slightly here Tuesday, following a similar move earlier in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The price for lead-free gasoline, industrial asphalt and black
asphalt dropped by 0.10 patacas to 0.13 patacas (1.25 U.S. cents
to 1.63 cents) per liter, or 1.66 percent to 4.27 percent.
</P>
<P>
The price cut was made by the Macao Oil Business Association,
who followed a world tide of price drop of oil products. The
previous price cut was in January.
</P>
<P>
After the cut, the price for lead-free gas will be for the first
time lower than the leaded gas, with a very slight gap. The
environment-friendly gas is being increasingly widely used in
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Macao now has about 80,000 vehicles running, against its
overall population of 420,000. 
</P>
