<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Far East Seeks Trade Opportunities in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Russia's largest business
delegation ever to visit Hong Kong, seeking opportunities for
economic and trade cooperation, made a presentation of the
Khabarovsk Territory located in the center of Russia's Far East
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center, Alexander Levintal, head of the delegation and
deputy governor of the Khabarovsk Territory, said that whoever
wants to carry out mutually beneficial cooperation with the region
will be welcome.
</P>
<P>
The Khabarovsk Territory, one of the largest regions in Russia,
is among the best developed areas in the Russian Far East, he
said, adding that it has established direct contacts with some
Chinese provinces like Heilongjiang and Liaoning, the American
states of Alaska and Oregon, the Japanese prefectures of Hyogo,
Aomori and Hokkaido, and also with some provinces of South Korea
and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The Khabarovsk Territory is rich in diverse natural resources
-- land, water, timber and other inland and marine biological
resources, and also numerous useful minerals. About 30 percent of
the Far East industrial potential is based in the territory,
including about a half of the mechanical engineering and chemical
enterprises, big facilities of timber cutting and processing
industry, Levintal said.
</P>
<P>
Director of the Russian Trade Association in Hong Kong Peter
Gordon told Xinhua that the seminar, accompanied by a related
photo exhibition, was the largest discussion ever organized by his
association in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Hong Kong remains an international trade and
financial center, Gordon said an increasing number of Russians
will come here to seek opportunities for cooperation not only in
the fields of trade and investment but also in joint manufacturing
and bilateral tourism.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
