<DOCNO> XIE19980317.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Icelandic Paintings Exhibition Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong began to stage for
the first time an exhibition of Icelandic art Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Icelandic Paintings of the 20th Century" in the Provisional
Urban Council's Museum of Art features 49 paintings by 28 artists.
</P>
<P>
The works cover a variety of subject matters and techniques.
They include figurative paintings portraying Icelandic landscapes
and people, and testify to the great diversity of contemporary
Icelandic art.
</P>
<P>
They display different artistic styles such as abstract art,
abstract expressionism, geometric abstraction, pop art, new
realism and minimal art "to express their vision and reflect both
new artistic concepts and traditional culture", said Provisional
Urban Councilor Ada Wong Ying-kay.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has always served as a bridge for Chinese and Western
cultural exchanges, Wong said. Through this exhibition, "Hong
Kong people can broaden their horizon as well as deepen their
understanding of European art and culture," she added.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is jointly presented by the Provisional Urban
Council and the Consulate of Iceland in Hong Kong and co-organized
by the Hong Kong Museum of Art and the National Gallery of
Iceland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
