<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong police captured 35
kilograms of "ice" and 2.5 kilograms of heroin here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A 42-year-old man was arrested in the operation.
</P>
<P>
At the man's residence, police confiscated 600,000 HK dollars
(77,000 U.S. dollars) in cash, which was suspected to be the
profit from drug dealings.
</P>
<P>
The seized drugs were estimated to have a market value of 11.2
million HK dollars (1.4 million U.S. dollars).  
