<HEADLINE> HK Papers Hail Election of New Chinese Leadership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The results of the elections
for China's top state and parliamentary leaders were applauded by
Hong Kong newspapers Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Almost every local newspaper ran special columns, publishing
commentaries or articles and photos about the country's new
leadership elected by deputies to the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC) in Beijing Monday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin was re-elected president of the People's Republic
of China (PRC) and chairman of the Central Military Commission, Li
Peng was elected chairman of the NPC Standing Committee and Hu
Jintao was elected vice-president of the PRC.
</P>
<P>
An editorial of the HK Commercial Daily said that the newly
elected trans-century leadership of China is trusted by the
people.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's re-election reflects his outstanding work and high
prestige have been fully recognized, and is conducive to the
stability of the whole leadership and to the continuity of the
principles and policies of the country, it said.
</P>
<P>
Ta Kung Pao said in a commentary that the outcome of the
elections shows the unity and coordination of China's top
leadership and the stability of the country.
</P>
<P>
The paper noted that under the Chinese leadership with Jiang at
the core, China is stable politically and its economy grows
rapidly and the people are living in peace and harmony.
</P>
<P>
It believed that the election results will boost the confidence
of 1.2 billion Chinese people and provide them a reliable
guarantee for advancing toward the 21st century, it added.
</P>
<P>
Other newspapers also praised the election of Hu Jintao as
vice-president, saying the young leadership will improve China's
image in the international arena. 
</P>
</TEXT>
