<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Customs Seizes Counterfeit Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong customs officers have
smashed a syndicate which distributed counterfeit leather goods
bearing a famous Italian trademark, the Government Information
Services reported here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Officers from the Intellectual Property Investigation Bureau
Monday raided four retail outlets of the syndicate, arresting four
women and capturing 2.2 million HK dollars (282,000 U.S. dollars)
worth of fake leather goods.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Customs carried out in-depth investigations after it
received a complaint lodged by the trademark owners and eventually
launched the operation.  
</P>
