<HEADLINE> Armstrong Pulls out of Milan-San Remo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- America's 1993 World champion Lance
Armstrong, who returned to professional circuit this season after
recovering from testicular cancer, will pull out of Saturday's
Milan-San Remo World Cup race, his US Postal team announced on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Armstrong has been forced by flu to withdraw from last week's
Paris-Nice race during the second stage and returned to the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The team did not reveal when the 26-year-old would next return
to the saddle. 
</P>
