<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower Tuesday on lack of
fresh leads.
</P>
<P>
Market was quiet as investors stayed on the sidelines to wait
for the new measures to stimulate the economy, to be announced by
Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim next week, a dealer said.
</P>
<P>
However, the 100-campanies benchmark Composite Index (CI)
stayed above the 700 level on strong support from local
institutionals. The CI lost 3.4 points to 700.21, the All Main
Board Emas Index 0.79 points to 177.3 and the Industrial Index
2.96 points to 1,266.78 while the Second Board Index dropped 1.46
points to 178.19.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers by 407 to 221 while 159 counters
were unchanged and 144 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 142.135 million shares valued
at 352.797 million ringgit (93.332 million U.S. dollars) from
121.462 million shares valued at 307.765 million ringgit (81.419
million dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the Main Board jumped to 128.369 million shares
valued at 320.022 million ringgit (84.66 million dollars) from
Monday's 108.56 million shares valued at 277.208 million ringgit
(73.335 million dollars). On the Second Board, volume rose to
13.766 million shares valued at 32.775 million ringgit (8.67
million dollars) from 12.902 million shares valued at 30.557
million ringgit (8.083 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market business deals fell to 4.148 million shares valued
at 21.399 million ringgit (5.66 million dollars) from 34.896
million shares valued at 69.632 million ringgit (18.421 million
dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 9.314
million shares traded on the Main Board, industrial products
8.172 million shares, construction 11.152 million shares,
trade/service 27.096 million shares, infrastructure 825,000
shares, finance 21.395 million shares, hotels 437,000 shares,
properties 13.394 million shares, plantations 7.339 million
shares, mining 489,000 shares, trusts 76,000 shares, closed-end
funds 24,000 shares and loans 28.657 million shares.  
</P>
</TEXT>
