<HEADLINE> Fire Accidents Lose Uganda Large Amount of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Fire accidents last year lost
Uganda about 2.9 billion Uganda Shillings (2.7 million
U.S.Dollars), ''The New Vision'' reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The correspondent loss of 1996 is some 900 million Uganda
Shillings, the paper quoted Jseph Mugisa, the police Chief Fire
Officer as saying.
</P>
<P>
Of the fire accidents, some 60 percent occured in the capital
Kampala where 800 million worth of property destroyed last year.
</P>
<P>
The most hit area is the eastern part of the capital city
where a central market in Mbale District was devastated last
September, said the paper.  
</P>
