<HEADLINE> Child Prostitutes Found in Johannesburg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Girls as young as eight
years old have been found working as prostitutes in certain
hotels in inner-city Johannesburg, local daily Sowetan reported
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Child prostitutes have added to the growing forms of
exploitation of children in South Africa, the newspaper quoted a
report by the Network Against Child Labor (NACL) as saying.
</P>
<P>
Of the 400,000 estimated child workers in South Africa, some
were girls who were forced or sold into prostitution in different
parts of the country, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Others between the age of 13 and 18 were working in Pretoria
and Midrand, a city between Pretoria and Johannesburg, as
prostitute.
</P>
<P>
Jackie Loffel, an official of the Johannesburg Child Welfare
Society, said child labor was another form of child abuse in
South Africa.
</P>
<P>
She said a large number of boys, particularly those seeking to
survive on the streets, were among those drawn into prostitution.
</P>
<P>
The NACL has organized a national campaign to mobilize action
against injustice contributing to child labor. The campaign
includes a national march due to start in Cape Town on March 21.
</P>
</TEXT>
