<HEADLINE> China Forms Largest Agricultural Enterprise Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Heilongjiang Beidahuang Land
Reclamation and Cultivation Enterprise group, the country's
largest state-owned agricultural enterprise group, was recently
established in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial land reclamation bureau noted
that goals for establishing the group center on ensuring the most
advantageous use of the natural resources, assets and technicians
of the state-owned farms, accelerating the opening-up steps, and
reforming related operations.
</P>
<P>
The Beidahuang land reclamation area includes 103 fully
mechanized medium- to large-sized state-owned farms which
cultivate well over 130,000 hectares and have total assets of
close to 22.45 billion yuan (2.7 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Beidahuang havested more than 8.5 billion kg of grain on
reclaimed land in 1997, with the group's farms also
producing powdered milk, high quality edible oil, spirits, farm
machinery and sugar beets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
