<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman Comments on Indonesian Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- China is confident that Indonesia
will overcome its current difficulties and return to the path of
healthy economic development, Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Zhu Bangzao said here today.
</P>
<P>
Responding to a reporter's question, Zhu said China is deeply
concerned and sympathizes with Indonesia for its economic
difficulties due to the Southeast Asian financial crisis, and
admires the Indonesian government and people for their unremitting
efforts in fighting the difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that President Soeharto is an outstanding leader of
Indonesia, and that under his leadership, Indonesia has scored
great achievements in developing the economy and raising its
people's living standards, playing an increasingly important role
in international and regional affairs over the past decades.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and Indonesia are two good neighbors, and
that China attaches great importance to developing good-neighborly
friendship with Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
After the Southeast Asian financial crisis occured, China took
an active part in International Monetary Fund's assistance plan
with Indonesia, providing some assistance in funds. He said that
the Chinese government has decided recently to give Indonesia a
free aid of three million US dollars worth of emergency medicine
and food supplies, in line with the Chinese people's friendly
sentiments for the Indonesian people. And the Chinese government
also expressed willingness to strengthen economic and trade
cooperation with Indonesia through providing export credits or the
form of barter trade.
</P>
<P>
He said that "we believe that under the leadership of President
Soeharto and through the efforts of the Indonesian government and
people and the assistance of the international community,
Indonesia will overcome its current difficulties and return to the
path of healthy economic development."  
