<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Computer Maker Has Global Ambition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Legend Group, a computer giant in
China, strives to rank among the world's top 10 information
technology firms in a decade, according to Legend President Liu
Chuanzhi.
</P>
<P>
At the present stage, Legend is to concentrate efforts on
expanding its domestic market share and gradually shift its
emphasis onto the international market, says Liu, who is here
attending the going annual session of the National People's
Congress, China's top lawmaking body.
</P>
<P>
Legend was set up in 1984 by 11 technicians in Beijing with an
initial capital of 200,000 yuan. It has been the largest desk-top
PC maker in China since 1996 with a domestic market share of 12
percent.
</P>
<P>
Its business turnover was 12.5 billion yuan last year and is
expected to reach 18 billion yuan this year, Liu says.
</P>
<P>
"Legend plans to raise its annual turnover to 3 billion US
dollars by the year 2000 to rank among the world's top 50 computer
firms," he says. "We aim to rank among the world's top ten by the
year 2008."
</P>
<P>
The PC maker has been exporting computer motherboards
to more than 40 countries and regions in the world, with its
total sales ranking fifth place in the world.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, it is possible that demand for PCs in China will reach
10 million a year to become the second biggest PC market in the
world, next only to the United States, he says.
</P>
<P>
At present, home-made computers enjoy a competitive edge over
imports on the domestic market thanks to their good performance
and low prices, he says.
</P>
<P>
"However," he adds, "Chinese PC producers should bring their
advantages into full play and offset their disadvantages,
especially in product development." 
</P>
</TEXT>
