<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks climbed 74
points, or 0.66 percent, to finish the session at 11,255.54
Tuesday afternoon following a gain of 124.51 points the previous
day.
</P>
<P>
The turnover totaled 6,813 million HK dollars (873 million U.S.
dollars), about 1,802 million HK dollars (231 U.S. dollars) more
than that of Monday.
</P>
<P>
This is the highest value of trade over the past seven
sessions.
</P>
<P>
Finance stocks continued to lead the way, advancing 120.09
points or 0.75 percent to 16,055.81 based on Monday's gains of
207.43 points, followed by two other sub-sectors of utilities and
commerce which registered a respective increase of 108.48 points
and 72.86 points.
</P>
<P>
Properties stocks dropped 23.72 points, or 0.17 percent, to
close at 14,346.99.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index opened up 86.48 points, or 0.77
percent to 11,268.02 Monday morning. The stocks closed its morning
session with the Hang Seng Index rising 97.54 points, or 0.88
percent, to 11,154.57. 
</P>
