<HEADLINE> Iranian FM Terms OIC Ministerial Meeting as </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi has termed as "constructive" the 25th assembly of the
foreign ministers of the Organization of the Islamic Conference
(OIC) which opened in Doha, Qatar on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to local press upon his return from the meeting Monday
evening, Kharrazi said that the meeting discussed issues
concerning the Muslim world, the regional problems and other
international topics "in a new atmosphere charged with cordiality,
sincerity and solidarity."
</P>
<P>
He said that the new spirit of cooperation and unity between
OIC member states had enhanced the block to reminisce of their
destiny and the issues of the region, particularly the question of
Israel.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister noted that Israel, which is in
possession of weapons of mass destruction and in pursuance of its
expansionist policy, posed a grave danger to all the countries in
the region.
</P>
<P>
He said that Israel's threat was taken up at the OIC foreign
ministers' assembly as a projected topic of discussion and that
the assembly needed to follow up the matter more seriously so that
the weapons of mass destruction in Israeli silos would be
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Also on the agenda of the assembly were regional, international
issues including that of Afghanistan, Iraq and the Middle East,
Kharrazi added.
</P>
<P>
Referring to his meetings with OIC foreign ministers, Kharrazi
said that the exchange of views were essential for preparing
ground for member countries to benefit from such
side talks.
</P>
<P>
On his one-day visit to Saudi Arabia and his meetings with top
ranking Saudi officials, he said that the relation between Saudi
Arabia and Iran was on the right course of expansion, particularly
after Chairman of Iran's State Expediency Council Hashemi
Rafsanjani visited Riyadh late February. 
</P>
