<HEADLINE> Trade Fair to Mark Founding of Hainan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Preparations are being made for an
April trade and economic cooperation fair to mark the 10th
anniversary of the founding of Hainan Province, China's largest
special economic zone.
</P>
<P>
The fair, scheduled for mid-April, is expected to attract large
contingents of entrepreneurs and business representatives from both
at home and abroad. Fierce competition has erupted for space in
the exhibition hall, which will cover more than 12,000 sq.m.,
according to Liu Xianzhang, director of the Hainan branch of the
China Council for Promotion of International Trade.
</P>
<P>
The province held the first fair in 1990, with ensuing
events through the end of 1996 resulting in the approval of export
contracts valued at 1.67 billion US dollars and investment
projects worth over 5.27 billion US dollars, including a paper
pulp project with an annual capacity of 600,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The province will offer online information concerning the fair
on the Internet. A local tourism agency and the local trade
promotion branch will offer free advertising for participating
enterprises and businesspeople via the same service, according to
Liu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
