<HEADLINE> Turkey Proposes Outline for Solution in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Turkey has proposed an outline for
stopping the continuing turbulence in Kosovo, Muslim region of
Yugoslavia, warning that the disorder may expand into a major
international crisis over all the Balkans unless a compromise is
reached.
</P>
<P>
Local Daily News Tuesday quoted State Minister Ahat Andican as
saying that leaders of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia and
representatives of the Kosovo people should immediately launch a
comprehensive dialog which should be aimed at finding a way to
facilitate the solution process.
</P>
<P>
Andican said that the dialog should also be aimed at restoring
the rights of all ethnic groups in Kosovo, which they enjoyed at
the time of Kosovo's autonomy.
</P>
<P>
The ultimate solution in Kosovo should guarantee the rights of
the Albanian majority and all ethnic minorities, including the
Turks, said the state minister, who is in charge of affairs for
Turks living abroad.
</P>
<P>
He added that effective measures should be taken with the help
of the international community to confront violent incidents that
may occur in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Andican said: "The rights of people living in Kosovo should be
given, before it is too late." 
</P>
</TEXT>
