<HEADLINE> Vietnam Issues Guideline on Encouraging Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnamese government on Monday
issued a 22-point guideline to encourage foreign direct investment.
</P>
<P>
The guideline, which contains detailed instructions to the
relevant ministries is aimed at simplifying administrative
procedures for foreign investment and creating favorable
conditions for foreign businesses.
</P>
<P>
Last year, foreign investment in Vietnam dropped to only 5.55
billion U.S. dollars, or 3.65 billion dollars lower than in the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Under the guideline, the ministries of finance, planning and
investment and land administration are requested to adjust the
levels of import duties and income tax and to draw up regulations
on land compensation and clearance for foreign investment
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
