<HEADLINE> Two Footballers Fined, Banned for Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's Paraguayan player
Casiano Delualle and Dalian's Hao Haidong have been each fined
1,000 yuan (120 US dollars) and banned for two games following
their violent behaviors in a Super Cup match last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Football Association said in a statement on Monday
that Delualle was disciplined for his physical reprisals against a
Dalian player who fouled him earlier. Delualle was flashed a red
card immediately.
</P>
<P>
The association said Hao, a national striker, run from the
bench and invaded the pitch to shove some Beijing players in a
dispute during the Super Cup game, which pitted professional
league champion Dalian against Chinese Football Association Cup
winner Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The two clubs were also fined 500 yuan each (60 dollars), while
Dalian's Sun Jihai and Beijing's Xie Chaoyang were warned for
their unsportsmanlike behaviors.
</P>
<P>
Three players, one from Dalian and two from Beijing, were sent
off during the volatile match held in the Southeastern coast city
of Wenzhou, Zhejiang province.
</P>
<P>
Beijing won the cup 2-1 on the very first sudden-death goal in
the Chinese soccer after the two sides drew 1-1 in 90 minutes.
</P>
</TEXT>
