<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liang Becomes China's 7th Grand Chess Master </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Chess player Liang Jinrong has
become the seventh International Grand Master from China, the
Chinese Chess Association said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Liang joined the ranks with Ye Rongguang, Ye Jiangchuan, Xie
Jun, Xu Jun, Wang Zili and Peng Xiaomin to receive the highest
title honored by the international chess body FIDE.
</P>
<P>
Liang, from southern Guangdong province, became one of the
first FIDE Masters from China in 1980.
</P>
<P>
He began to compete in the national tournaments in 1974 and won
the national title in 1995. 
