<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Netherlands-aided Centers to Test for Newborn Baby Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Netherlands-aided centers to
test for newborn baby diseases have opened in Hunan, Henan and
Jiangxi provinces and the cities of Shanghai and Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Ministry of Health said the centers, first
of a kind in China that receive blood tests of newborn babies, are
being established to control genetotrophic and congenital
secretory diseases.
</P>
<P>
Wallac Corp. from the Netherlands provides the facilities for
the centers and offers technical training for Chinese doctors. The
cooperative project will last three years.
</P>
<P>
The congenital diseases of newborn babies are mainly abnormal
functioning of thyroid and phenylketonuria (PKU) which hinder the
development of babies' intelligence.
</P>
<P>
During the trial period, the Hunan center has performed blood
tests for more than 7,000 newborn babies; three cases of PKU were
discovered. After a period of treatment, the three children are
doing well.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Health official said China will gradually
establish centers in other provinces and municipalities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
