<HEADLINE> Air Zimbabwe to Operate Flights to London for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Air Zimbabwe will start operating
long-haul flights to London for Air Malawi and Zambia Express
from next month, The Herald reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The airline is consolidating its ties with regional carriers
to try to improve its viability.
</P>
<P>
As competition within the skies stiffens, survival of smaller
airlines such as Air Zimbabwe will depend on their ability to
withstand the competition and build alliances with both large and
small carriers.
</P>
<P>
Air Zimbabwe will be maximizing the use of its Boeing 767
aircraft by offering its excess capacity to Air Malawi and Zambia
Express.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for Air Zimbabwe, David Mwenga,
said that the flights to London would be strictly for Air
Malawi and Zambia Express and would originate from Lusaka and
Lilongwe.
</P>
<P>
"Air Zimbabwe will provide the aircraft and cockpit crew while
the two airlines would provide cabin crew from their capitals,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Preparations for the flights have started, with cabin crews
from both Air Malawi and Zambia Express attending a
familiarization flight safety exercise in Harare recently.
</P>
