<HEADLINE> February Rise in Railway Transportation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- China's railway system
transported an average 2.92 million passengers daily during
February, up 4.1 percent on the 1997 period, according to the
Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
The number of long-distance passengers travelling more than
500 km stood at 856,000 in a day, a year-on-year rise of 26.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
The railway system fulfilled transportation targets for key
materials, including iron and steel, gold, minerals, metallurgical
materials, timber, fertilizer and grain.
</P>
<P>
An average of 189,000 TEU containers (1.59 million tons) were
transported on a daily basis, up 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
The ministry report indicates the absence of railway
transportation or production accidents during February.
</P>
<P>
Some 138 million people travelled by rail during the 50 days
before, during and after Spring Festival, the traditional major
Chinese holiday which commenced January 28. Large numbers of
college students and out-of-towners traditionally return to home
for family reunions during the period.
</P>
<P>
The number of people travelling represented a 2.3 percent rise
on the 1997 Spring Festival period, with the number of
long-distance travellers increasing by 18.3 percent to 39.2
million people.
</P>
<P>
The highest daily transportation volume during the period hit a
record 3.41 million people, according to the ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
