<HEADLINE> Tibetan Team to Scale World's Third Highest Peak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A mountaineering team from the
Tibetan Autonomous Region has set off for Nepal to scale in May
Mt. Kanchenjunga, the third highest in the world.
</P>
<P>
The 10-men team is expected to arrive at the foot of the
mountain in the end of April and began their journey to the
8,586-meter peak in early May.
</P>
<P>
The mountain, famous for its treacherous climbing condition and
glaciers, was conquered for the first time by four members from a
British team on May 25, 1955.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, the Tibetan team made a plan to conquer in ten years
all 14 mountains above 8,000 meters and has since successfully
scaled seven of them. 
