<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The 621 cooperative in central
China's Hunan Province at the end of last year employed more than
1,000 redundant workers and had total sales of over 50 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Changsha Railway Corporation Trade Union established
consumer cooperative services in June last year. The union has
since opened a distribution center, two chain stores and 90 branch
outlets.
</P>
<P>
