<HEADLINE> Beijing Pools Housing Accumulation Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has accumulated funds of
more than 3.1 billion yuan (373 million US dollars) since the
initiation of housing reform some five years ago.
</P>
<P>
Institutional organizations throughout the city have introduced
the housing funds accumulation system, with some 2.2 million
workers contributing funds for housing purchases.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Housing Capital Administration Center has granted
loans of 3.8 billion yuan, including loans of 100 million to
individuals.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the center has provided support for some 60-odd
residential construction projects with total floor space of over
four million square meters.
</P>
<P>
Beijing had sold 420,000 state-owned apartments, or 20 percent
of the total, to individuals by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has completed construction of six million
sq.m. of housing annually in recent years, with last year's figure
hitting a record eight million square meters.
</P>
<P>
The center will join Beijing branches of the China Construction
Bank and Industrial and Commercial Bank of China in offering
housing loans to individuals during 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
