<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
finished higher on Tuesday, boosted by another record close on
Wall Street overnight.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 18 points higher at 2,311 with a
turnover of 104 million dollars (60 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom led the rises as investors reacted positively to
Ameritech's plan to sell down its 25 percent share in the company.
Telecom shares ended the day 8 cents higher to 850 cents.
</P>
<P>
Other firmer main leaders were Air New Zealand and Brierley
Investment, up 2 cents to 204 cents and 116 cents respectively.
Fletcher Building climbed 10 cents to 410 cents and Fletcher Paper
gained 9 cents to 260 cents.
</P>
<P>
Among the weaker leaders, Carter Holt Harvey and Fletcher
Energy each eased 2 cents to 260 cents and 593 cents respectively.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
