<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agreement Reached for Sino-US Nonwoven Cloth Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 17 (Xinhua) -- US-based PCI Co. and the Hainan
Xinlong Nonwoven Cloth Industrial Co. Ltd. recently signed a
framework agreement calling for long-term cooperation to establish
the largest nonwoven fabric enterprise in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The Hainan Xinlong Nonwoven Cloth Mill, a project established
to mark the 10 anniversary of the founding of Hainan Province
which will fall in April, will have an annual production capacity
of 30,000 tons of nonwoven cloth. The venture will be the largest
of its kind in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The China National Textile Council promoted the project as part
of an effort to establish the China Nonwoven Industrial City in
the provincial capital city.
</P>
<P>
First phase construction will be completed at a cost of 100
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Hainan officials recently joined PCI managers in in-depth
discussions concerning the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
