<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia Eludes China's Growing Worldwide Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- China's exports to most
continents grew by wide margins during the first two months of
1998, according to statistics released by China's General
Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
Exports to North America grew by 23.3 percent to 4.78 billion
US dollar; Europe by 36 percent to 4.69 billion; Latin America by
36 percent to 680 million; Africa by 27.2 percent to 470 million;
and Oceania by 16.9 percent to 370 million.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Asian countries witnessed sluggish growth due to
financial turmoil in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
