<HEADLINE> Foreign Banks Stop Operations in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Four representative offices of
foreign banks have stopped operations in Vietnam, an official
announcement released here said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the foreign banks which have closed their offices are
the Chohung Bank and Commercial Bank of South Korea, the Farmer
Bank and Ayudhya Public Bank of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The suspended operations of these offices was due to financial
difficulties faced by their countries, the announcement said.
</P>
