<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Russia Long for WTO Memberships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Worldwide economic cooperation could
be hardly successful as some big nations are still out of the
World Trade Organization (WTO), Ukrainian and Russian officials
said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
As about the "big nations," senior Ukrainian and Russian
officials at a consultation roundtable on trade issues were
referring to, among others, Russia, China and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which ended Monday, was attended by Ukraine's
First Deputy Foreign Economic Relations and Trade Minister Andrei
Goncharuk and his Russian counterpart Georgy Gabunya.
</P>
<P>
The two sides signed a protocol to expand their trade
cooperation and further the consultation process.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that they would be unlikely to cooperate
effectively with European and other countries around the world if
they are not be allowed into the WTO.
</P>
<P>
Being shut out from the world trade regime, Goncharuk said,
Ukraine could hardly get around with issues such as trade
protection, and attract foreign investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
