<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia-Europe University Center to Be in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Education Minister
Najib Tun Razak said Tuesday that a center will be set up here
soon to provide the infrastructure for enhancing Asia-Europe
university relations.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the proposed center, to be known as the
"Asia-Europe University Center" is expected to be endorsed by
ministers attending next month's Second Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM)
in London, he told reporters here after opening a seminar on
"Asia-Europe Educational Link: Laying The Foundation."
</P>
<P>
He said that besides serving as a vehicle for networking
activities between Asia and Europe in university relations, the
center would also be used as a medium for creating a system to
ensure better information flow and initiate cooperative dialogues
and seminars.
</P>
<P>
The idea of closer cooperation between Asia and Europe beyond
traditional ties was mooted by Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad during the inaugural ASEM in Bangkok two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Najib said details about the center are still confidential
pending the tabling of the proposal at the forthcoming ASEM.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in his speech at the seminar, Najib said people of the
two continents would be able to reach a higher level of
understanding through the educational process.
</P>
<P>
He said it is time for Asia and Europe to appreciate each other
and no longer treat the two continents as separate entities based
on their economic and trade linkages.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
