<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian to Draw up Economic Policy By Mid-April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Italian government will hammer
out its economic policy document by April 15 to 20, said Italian
treasury minister on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Carlo Azegli Ciampi said, however, that there was not enough
time for the document to be passed by parliament by May 2, when
the European Union would decide on the first member states to join
the European single currency.
</P>
<P>
By April 15-20, certain aspects of the document, including the
labor cost pact and other base elements, would have been examined
by the social parties, he said.
</P>
<P>
Italy is substantially in line with all parameters, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
