<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech's Population Keeps Decreasing In 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The population of the Czech
Republic dropped again last year, despite official encouragement
for couples to have more children.
</P>
<P>
Josef Zabrasky, spokesman of the Czech State Census Bureau,
said Tuesday that the population stood at 10.299 million, 10,012
less than the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Though many efforts have been tried by the authority to
encourage child-bearing, few of them succeed, said Zabrasky.
</P>
<P>
But the population is also aging and 25 percent of Czechs are
expected to be aged 60 or over by the year 2015, he said.
</P>
<P>
The population was not expected to rise for some time, the
spokesman said. It is estimated that the population of the Czech
Republic will fall below 10 million for the first time in 2014.
</P>
</TEXT>
