<HEADLINE> Pudong Purses Ambitious Housing Construction Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area in Shanghai,
China's largest city, plans to complete construction of 10 million
sq.m. of housing over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investments are helping to fund 40 percent of the
ambitious project.
</P>
<P>
The 65 billion yuan earmarked for land development and housing
construction since 1990 accounts for 37.8 percent of total real
estate investment in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
Pudong's 800-odd registered real estate companies currently
employ over 23,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Plans for the next three years call for Pudong to complete some
three million sq.m. of housing annually, with the new value-added
accounting for 8-10 percent of the zone's annual GDP.
</P>
<P>
Funds will also be earmarked for the construction of
residential housing in areas along the Huangpu River. Individuals
will be encouraged to purchase housing and real estate sales are
expected to hit 15 billion yuan annually.
</P>
<P>
Emphasis will be placed on leases and outright sales of
facilities in the Xiaolujiazui Financial Center.  
</P>
