<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Concerned Over Threat of Widespread Forest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's new State Minister of
Environment Juwono Sudarsono has declared his intention to instill
"a sense of crisis" in the public over the threat of widespread
forest fires in the country.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the declaration Monday after taking the oath
at the Merdeka Palace, newspapers reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that forest fires would damage Indonesia's
international image if the nation failed to properly handle the
recurring problem.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two months, fires have been raging over almost
80,000 hectares of forest and brush in the country's East
Kalimantan province bordering the Malaysian states of Sarawak and
Sabah on the island of Borneo.
</P>
<P>
Head of the provincial Environmental Impact Management Agency
Awang Farouk Ishak said Monday that 76,949.4 hectares of forest
have been destroyed by fires this year, causing losses of up to 22
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Local people in the province and residents of neighboring
Singapore and Malaysia have expressed concern that choking smog,
caused by massive fires in Sumatra and Kalimantan last year, will
return, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 million people in Kalimantan and Sumatra were exposed
to hazardous haze caused by fires which burned for around nine
months last year. The World Wide Fund for Nature said that the
haze cost Indonesia over 900 million U.S. dollars in short-term
health costs alone.
</P>
<P>
This year, more than 2,000 East Kalimantan residents have
reportedly suffered respiratory ailments caused by haze over the
past two months.
</P>
<P>
Juwono, who is also chairman of the Environment Impact
Management Agency, said that to help counter the wide regional and
international impact of this year's fires, the country would have
to launch an "all-out environmental diplomacy drive".
</P>
<P>
"We must work hard in order to be able to cope with
environmental impact," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
