<HEADLINE> Zhangzhou Attracts More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Official statistics show that
Zhangzhou, a coastal city in east China's Fujian Province,
continues to enjoy robust growth in foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Zhangzhou approved the founding of 51 overseas-funded
enterprises in the first two months of this year, with contracted
foreign investments totaling 122 million US dollars, up 150
percent on the 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded enterprises recorded a total industrial output
value of 2.12 billion yuan for the first two months, up 59.1
percent on a year-on-year basis, with exports growing by 12.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
Zhangzhou's contracted overseas investment totalled 4.88
billion US dollars for the period between 1993 and October 1997,
with allocated investments hitting 1.9 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, Zhangzhou has attempted to improve its environment
by investing a total of four billion yuan in infrastructure
construction, up three-fold on the total figure for the previous
13 year period. 
