<HEADLINE> Romania to Experience Zero Growth, Inflation Decrease in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The rate of inflation in
Romania is expected to plummet to 45 percent this year from 151.4
percent in 1997, according to the government's new draft budget.
</P>
<P>
But the forecast also predicts the economy will seize up with a
zero growth rate in 1998, but no reason for the halt was given.
</P>
<P>
The government is expected to approve the draft budget and the
proposed spending of 14.89 billion U.S. dollars on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The gross domestic product is likely to reach 42.83 billion
dollars, an increase of more than 30 percent from last year's 30.1
billion dollars, the draft said.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry will be allotted 894.69 million dollars
under the draft, 1.27 billion dollars will go to the Health
Ministry and 1.53 billion dollars to the Education Ministry.
</P>
</TEXT>
