<HEADLINE> Anhui Promotes Spark Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province, one of
the country's major grain production bases, has vowed to promote
the Spark Program in order to accelerate growth in the rural
sector.
</P>
<P>
The provincial plan is part of the national program designed to
introduce science and technology to agricultural production. The
effort will focus on densely populated areas in northern Anhui,
the major production area for grain, cotton and oil-bearing crops.
</P>
<P>
The plan calls for the establishment of concentrated
technological zones in one third of townships in the region by the
year 2000. Each zone is expected to have 15-odd companies with an
annual sales of 300-500 million yuan and pretax profits of 30-50
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In addition, plans call for the zone to achieve a 10 percent
annual increase rate in the value-added new and high technology
industries, and each zone will train some one million people.
</P>
<P>
Group companies with annual output values of between 500
million and two billion yuan each will be encouraged to enter the
food processing, aquatics, forestry, herbal medicines, forage crop
and light industrial sectors.
</P>
<P>
A consulting group of experts from institutes of higher
education will be formed to provide technical assistance.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
