<HEADLINE> Health of Italian President Stable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Scalfaro's
condition was improving on Monday after he was taken to hospital
with influenza at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said the president passed a series of tests on Monday,
including a check for blood vessel blockages around his heart.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro was taken to Rome's Gemelli hospital on Saturday after
a lingering bout of influenza, which forced him to cancel state
visits to China, Israel and Syria.
</P>
<P>
"President Scalfaro's tests have been completed and they
couldn't have gone better," said Attillio Maseri, director of the
hospital's cardiology unit. "There is nothing at all to worry
about."
</P>
<P>
Maseri said that Scalfaro would be released from hospital on
Wednesday. 
