<HEADLINE> Romanians Have a Passion For Big Macs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 16 (Xinhua) -- For nearly three years,
McDonalds has been massively penetrating the Romanian market,
owning 28 restaurants at present in more than nine cities and
towns.
</P>
<P>
Marin Alecu, general manager of the McDonalds in Romania, told
Adevarul Economic Weekly (The Economic Truth) the reason for such
success.
</P>
<P>
"It is rooted in the conclusion drawn after quite detailed
market surveys and testing the company has been carrying out since
1993", he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Romanians have proved to be great fans of the American
life style. The estimate was later confirmed and it still stands
true.
</P>
<P>
"The country's potential is very high and McDonalds is
preparing itself for the future," Alecu said.
</P>
<P>
"Last year, we offered 32,000 (U.S.) dollars for studies aimed
at helping us understand what was going on in the Romanian society
and economy, and especially what we were supposed to do in order
to increase sales", Alecu said. "The Romanians like McDonalds'
offers, and our pricing policy."
</P>
<P>
The investment by McDonalds in Romania has amounted to about 35
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
