<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Precious Species Thriving in Guizhou Nature Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Maolan state-level nature
reserve in southwest China's Guizhou Province has become one of
the gene data banks of precious species in China.
</P>
<P>
Located in Libou County -- an area between the provinces of
Yunan and Guizhou and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region -- the
Maolan forest protection zone covers 21,285 hectares.
</P>
<P>
With a forest coverage rate of 92 percent, the region has a
distinct environmental feature. After incessant research on the
nature reserve's environment, both domestic and foreign experts
concluded that the zone is a rare natural laboratory and precious
gene data bank.
</P>
<P>
"The nature reserve boasts over 1,600 kinds of plants and more
than 300 kinds of vertebrates," said Wei Lumin, deputy director of
the protection department of the reserve.
</P>
<P>
He said that the precious tree species include the fir of the
genus ormosia, emmenopterys henryi, dysosma versipellis, and
cephaaalotaxus oliveri, most of which are under top state
protection.
</P>
<P>
Scientific observations also have revealed that the reserve is
home to such endangered animal species as the clouded leopard,
tiger and python, as well as 103 kinds of birds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980317.0218 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Caltex Settles Down in North China's Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- US-based Caltex Oil Company
recently broke ground for construction of a lubricating oil
subsidiary in the bonded zone in north China's Tianjin Port.
</P>
<P>
Caltex Tianjin Lubricating Oil Co. Ltd. will be established at
a cost 30 million US dollars. The first phase will involve the
construction of facilities covering 30,000 square meters. The
plant will bottle refined lubricating oil and additives, and will
have extensive facilities for storing raw materials.
</P>
<P>
Caltex Tianjin will produce different grades of lubricating oil
and will market most of its products in north China, with a
portion of output going to the overseas market.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for the installation of all equipment by the end of
next February.
</P>
<P>
Caltex Oil Co. has established subsidiary operations in 64
countries and regions, including Africa, the Middle East and the
Asia-Pacific Region. The company's annual output value exceeds 18
billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
