<HEADLINE> Romanian Mission to Seek NATO Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Romania will send a diplomatic
mission to the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)
headquarters in Brussels on Wednesday to bolster its claims to
join the alliance.
</P>
<P>
The mission will present the importance of the role Romania
plays in the stability of the region and the whole continent, said
Ambassador Lazar Comanescu, who is to lead the 14-member mission.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Romania's capability, Comanescu said there is a
need for strengthening and speeding up the reform process so that
the country's demarche acquires a higher credibility.
</P>
<P>
Romania will also take measures to gain more support over its
bid to join the NATO.
</P>
<P>
Comanescu said the mission will make every effort to make sure
Romania is integrated into the NATO in 1999. 
</P>
