<HEADLINE> More Overseas Visitors Tour Southwest China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 270,000 overseas people
visited southwest China's Sichuan Province last year, an increase
of more than 50 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists from Asia, Europe and the United States
showed the biggest increase while more than 90,000 visitors came
from other Asian countries in 1997, up more than 40 percent from
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the number of tourists from Thailand grew more than
170 percent over the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
The province has been attracting an increasing number of
overseas visitors because of local resorts, scenic spots and
cultural heritage combined with improvements in the local
infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The province has opened air routes linking more than 60
domestic cities as well as overseas cities like Singapore and
Bangkok. 
</P>
</TEXT>
