<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Missile, Artillery Forces Department Chief Sacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 16 (Xinhua) - The army officer in charge of
Bulgaria's missile and artillery forces has been dismissed by the
government for misconduct.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian President Petar Stoyanov removed Major General Angel
Marin from his post as Acting Chief of Missile and Artillery
Forces, said the presidential secretariat on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Defense Minister Georgi Ananiev said Marin
was sacked at the recommendation of the Council of Ministers.
</P>
<P>
Marin abused his military position and disclosed official
secrets, alleged Ananiev.
</P>
<P>
The general had also issued a statement voicing his disapproval
of reforms of in the army which violated Bulgaria's Defense and
Armed Forces Act, said Ananiev.
</P>
<P>
His actions would be referred to the Armed Forces Prosecutor's
Office, the defense minister added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
