<HEADLINE> Shandong to Hold Tourism Activity about Confucius </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Qufu, the home of Confucius, will
be host for a series of tourism activities Sept. 20-Oct. 5 to
honor the 2,549th anniversary of the great master's birth.
</P>
<P>
The activities will include theatrical performances, memorial
ceremonies, prayer sessions, seminars and exhibitions of folk
customs in and around Qufu in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Many descendents of Confucius will return to Qufu to pay homage
to the master on Sept. 29, Confucius' birthday.
</P>
<P>
Confucius, one of the most famous philosophers in ancient
China, spread his doctrines to both political figures and ordinary
citizens, calling on them to love each other and adhere to secular
rules. Confucianism remains popular in many Asian countries and
regions even today.
</P>
<P>
The event is being sponsored by the government of Qufu city,
the China Kanghui Travel Agency and the China Confucius
Foundation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
