<HEADLINE> Lee Resigns as Chairman of Manchester City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Francis Lee resigned as chairman
of English first division club Manchester City on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Lee, who also quit as a director, will be replaced by director
David Bernstein at the helm of the club currently languishing in
the relegation zone.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Joe Royle took over from Frank Clark as manager at
the club but Lee has remained under fierce criticism from the fans
as the team continued to suffer defeats on the pitch. 
</P>
</TEXT>
