<HEADLINE> Surprising Selection of Alonso for Davis Cup Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Davis Cup captain Manuel
Santana on Monday made a surprising selection of Julian Alonso for
the Davis Cup men's tennis team against Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Alonso, ranked 43rd in the world, teams up with Alex Corretja,
Carlos Moya and Javier Sanchez in a tie against Brazil in Porto
Alegre from April 3-5.
</P>
<P>
Six Spanish men not selected for the squad are above Alonso in
the ATP rankings.
</P>
<P>
Santana said he was impressed by Alonso's improvement and the
choice was also "an experiment". 
</P>
</TEXT>
