<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Pudong New Area Shows Marked Increase in Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area in Shanghai
handled 600 million U.S. dollars of exports during the first two
months of this year, a 37 percent rise from the same period in
1997, despite the influence of Southeast Asia's monetary crisis.
</P>
<P>
Of the export amount, 156 million U.S. dollars were brought in
by local overseas-funded enterprises, up 247 percent over the same
period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Pudong now has 89 foreign trade companies set up by domestic
businesses. Exports handled by the foreign companies reached 13.77
million U.S. dollars during the two-month period.
</P>
<P>
Because of improvements in export-oriented processing trade,
the Waigaoqiao Free Trade Zone in Pudong registered 89 million
U.S. dollars of exports, up 72 percent over the year-ago period.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, exports in Pudong have grown 30 percent
annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
