<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi To Spread Environmentally Friendly Energy Techniques </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANXI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Shanxi Province in north China is
spreading the use of solar energy and marsh gas as substitute
energy sources to relieve the energy shortage and improve the
environment.
</P>
<P>
Almost half of Shanxi Province is suffering from an energy
shortage because of backward natural and economic conditions,
which has led to the deterioration of the environment.
</P>
<P>
"The spread of the environmentally friendly energy techniques
has brought relief to the environment," said an official with the
provincial energy protection station.
</P>
<P>
He said the province has developed energy-efficient stoves for
1.9 million households, solar-powered water heaters for more than
10,000 households, 4,600 hectares of solar greenhouses, and nearly
70,000 hectares of plastic-covered farmland.
</P>
<P>
The spread of these techniques has saved energy amounting to
burning 2 million tons of coal, and harmful emissions have also
been cut by more than 5 million tons each year.
</P>
<P>
The widespread use of marsh gas as rural household's new energy
has saved 2 million tons of firewood, reducing the use of chemical
fertilizers, which has brought a relief to air and ground
pollution.
</P>
<P>
"Although the increasing energy demand has posed a threat to
environmental protection, these environmental friendly energy
techniques will be adopted more widely," said the official.
</P>
<P>
The province has also combined the use of marsh gas with solar
greenhouses to develop ecological agriculture, which has increased
the agricultural output, as well as improving the rural
environment and hygienic conditions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
