<DOCNO> XIE19980317.0244 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Steel Corporation Honored for Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Baogang, one of China's biggest
iron and steel corporations in Shanghai, has received ISO14001
certification recently for its internationally advanced
environmental administration.
</P>
<P>
The recognition by the International Standard Organization
(ISO) of Baogang's efforts in environmental protection has made it
the first in China's metallurgy industry to reach international
environmental protection levels.
</P>
<P>
The huge enterprise adopted environmental protection measures
when it was still under construction. The investment in
environmental protection reached 1.04 billion yuan (120 million
U.S. dollars) during its first and second phases, and the
investment accounted for 5.3 percent of the total investment in
equipment during the third phase.
</P>
<P>
"Baogang has expanded its environmental protection from solo
pollution treatment to saving resources and energy, and
comprehensive utilization of resources," said Xie Qihua, Baogang's
general manager.
</P>
<P>
"The whole production process is being controlled against
pollution, and everyone is held responsible for environmental
protection. Baogang has already been turned into an ecologically
friendly 'clean factory' according to evaluations from various
aspects," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ninety-eight percent of the enterprise's pollutants were
qualified to be discharged and the amount of sulfur dioxide and
carbon monoxide in the air conformed to the state standards set
for first-degree air quality, according to a survey conducted last
year.
</P>
<P>
The enterprise also has achieved an economic return of 400
million yuan in its efforts to efficiently use energy and raw
materials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
