<HEADLINE> Rozental to Miss World Cup Finals due to Knee Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Chilean striker Seb Rozental of
Glasgow Rangers, will certainly miss the World Cup finals in
France due to another operation on his knee, team manager Walter
Smith said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Smith confirmed that Rozental was set to undergo a third knee
operation. The latest injury is with the same knee, but is
unconnected to the previous ligament damage which has sidelined
him for almost a year.
</P>
<P>
The operation will surely forbid the Chilean from playing this
summer's World Cup in France.
</P>
<P>
The four million pound (6.5 million U. S. dollars) signing from
Universidad Catolica is expected to return home for the surgery.
</P>
</TEXT>
