<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kidd Named NBA Player of the Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Jason Kidd, guard of the
Phoenix Suns who helped guide his team to a 4-0 record, was named
NBA Player of the Week for the period ending Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kidd averaged 16.0 points, 10.0 assists, 6.5 rebounds and 3.0
steals in 36 minutes per game. He shot 62 percent (28-of-45) from
the floor, ranked second in the league in assists, tied for fourth
in steals and eighth in shooting.
</P>
<P>
Kidd began the week Monday with 12 points, 13 assists and four
rebounds in a 134-105 rout of the Los Angeles Clippers, and ended
it with his 18th career triple-double -- 20 points, 13 boards and
12 assists -- in a 100-90 victory over Dallas on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
