<HEADLINE> Dow Crosses over 8,700 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 16 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks rose sharply on
Monday with the Dow Jones industrial average soaring 116.33 to
close at 8,718.85, the first time the barometer of the 30
blue-chip companies finished above 8,700.
</P>
<P>
With today's gains, the Dow has risen 810.60 points or 10.25
percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Advances of the Dow's financial components such as J.P. Morgan,
American Express and others such as Alcoa and Sears Roebuck
contributed to the boost of the benchmark indicator Monday.
</P>
<P>
Broader market indicators also gained with the technology heavy
Nasdaq composite index rising 16.52 to 1,788.18, smashing the
February 26's record close of 1,777.11.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 stock list jumped 10.66 to 1,079.27
and the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) composite index was up 4.77
to 561.94.
</P>
<P>
On the NYSE, advancing issues led decliners 3-2 with 1,809 up,
1,174 down and 513 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Transaction volume totaled 546.83 million shares against 594.58
million shares on Friday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
