<HEADLINE> Aerospace &AMP; Defense Firms Poised for Revenue Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Globalization and product
innovation are the principal strategies for the growth of
aerospace and defense (A&AMP;D) industry in the next century, a study
found.
</P>
<P>
A&AMP;D executives surveyed by U.S. service company Deloitte &AMP;
Touche said they anticipate that 31 percent of their revenue will
be derived from new products introduced in the next three years.
</P>
<P>
This is a phenomenal rise from last year's near 20 percent
level, said the company in its 1998 Vision in Manufacturing global
CEO study, released on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The executives pointed out that A&AMP;D companies are diversifying
into new sectors such as telecommunications and space technology,
the fastest growing segments in the industry.
</P>
<P>
While North America and Western Europe continue to be important
targets for A&AMP;D expansion overseas, Asia Pacific is the choice
destination for almost 90 percent of North American and European
A&AMP;D executives, despite the continued currency crisis in the
region, analysts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
