<HEADLINE> UNDP to Assist Cuba in Its Economic Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Programme (UNDP) and the Government of Cuba have
launched a new program to implement a range of macro-economic
reforms in such areas as budget planning, social security and
banking, a release from UNDP said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The release said staff training will be provided for managers
in several key state institutions, including the central bank
and the Ministry of Economy and Planning.
</P>
<P>
UNDP is providing 1.15 million U.S. dollars in funds and Norway
will provide 300,000 U.S. dollars. Brazil, Mexico and Chile will
send economic experts to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
"The economic reform program is of strategic significance to
Cuba," Ariel Francais, the UNDP Resident Representative in
Havana, was quoted as saying.  
</P>
