<HEADLINE> Boeing Says FAA Approved New Generation 737-800 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Airplane maker Boeing said its
new generation model of 737-800 has earned type certification from
the U.S. Federal Aviation Administration and is ready to enter
into passenger service.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Continental and Hapag-Lloyd of Germany are among the first
customers to take delivery this year of the plane capable of
carrying 160-189 passengers, it said in a press release on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The new Boeing 737 family, also including 600, 700 and 900
models, is featured by larger wings, higher cruise speed, greater
range than the previous models and by improvements in noise, fuel
burn, thrust and maintenance costs, the company said.
</P>
<P>
Since the program's launch, orders have been placed for 840 new
generation Boeing 737s, according to company statistics. 
</P>
