<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
looks forward to a return visit to China and meeting with Chinese
President Jiang Zemin "sooner rather than later," said White House
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We have... enjoyed high-level exchanges with the People's
Republic (of China) that included successful summit meetings with
President Clinton," said White House spokesman Mike McCurry.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, a White House spokesman announced that Clinton has
decided to move the summit with Jiang up to June or July from a
later date this year.
</P>
<P>
