June or possibly going into the early part of July," said James
Steinberg, deputy national security advisor.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue our cooperative work on a broad range of
things that reflect the expansive nature of this bilateral
relationship, while not missing the opportunity for dialogue and
exchange of views on those areas in which there are clear
differences between our two governments," said McCurry.
</P>
<P>
Jiang visited the United States last October. It was the first
visit to the U.S. by a Chinese head of state in 12 years. 
