<HEADLINE> Qatar's Emir to Visit Egypt on Mending Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Qatar's Emir Sheikh Hamad bin
Khalifa al-Thani is due to visit Egypt later this month to patch
up relations between the two countries, a Qatari government
official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari Foreign Ministry's spokesman Fawaz al Attiyah was
quoted by the Qatari news agency as saying that the emir would go
to Cairo on March 23 for talks with Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak "to iron out differences" between Doha and Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries have been strained after a
war of words between them on the Qatar-hosted the fourth Middle
East and North Africa economic conference in last November. Egypt
joined Arab states in boycotting the meeting to protest against
Israel's participation.
</P>
<P>
The row worsened when Doha accused Cairo of masterminding a
failed attempt to topple the Qatari government in 1996. Egypt has
denied the allegations.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia's King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz mediated in a meeting
between the Qatari emir and the Egyptian president in Riyadh last
December to end the rift.
</P>
<P>
But tension increased again after Cairo imposed visa
requirements on Qatari visitors while Doha sacked hundreds of
Egyptian employees working in some Qatari governmental
departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
