<HEADLINE> Palestinian Official Warns Against Settlers' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The head of Palestinian
security forces in West Bank Jibril Rajoub warned Monday Jewish
settlers against intruding Palestinian-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in Hebron, Rajoub said any settlers who entered
the self-rule areas to harm Palestinians could not come out
alive. He was apparently commenting on the incident Friday night
when a group of Jewish settlers entered the Palestinian-rule
area of Hebron and triggered clashes with Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Seventeen people, including eight Palestinian journalists, were
hurt during the clashes as Israeli soldiers fired rubber
bullets to disperse the Palestinian protesters. One Israeli
soldier and two border policemen were also wounded in the
rioting.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police have begun investigating the incident, and
issued summons to fifteen Jewish settlers in Hebron who
organized the Friday march into the Palestinian area of the
divided city. The settlers claimed that they staged the protest
only after shots were fired at the Abu Sneineh quarter.
</P>
<P>
Until Monday, most of the settlers summoned have ignored
the police summons. Hebron settlers' spokesman Naomi Arnon said
most of the organizers were from other areas.
</P>
<P>
The recent wave of Israeli-Palestinian clashes was sparked by
the Tuesday killing of three Palestinians by Israeli soldiers at
a roadblock near Hebron.
</P>
<P>
About one hundred Palestinian protesters in the territories
have been wounded by Israeli soldiers. With the help of
Palestinian police to calm the tension, the violence began
subsiding in the territories from Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
