<HEADLINE> SAARC Supports Setting up Cotton Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chamber of Commerce and
Industry (CCI) of the South Asian Association for Regional
Cooperation (SAARC) strongly supported the suggestion to form a
SAARC cotton forum to maximize the benefits from cotton.
</P>
<P>
The message came at a meeting Monday in Karachi between the
members of the Karachi Cotton Association (KCA) and SAARC Chamber
of Commerce and Industry.
</P>
<P>
Earlier KCA had proposed to have a cotton association or
committee within SAARC to look after the interests of
cotton-producing member countries.
</P>
<P>
Chaudary Mirani, member of the executive committee of the SAARC
Chamber of Commerce and Industry, said that western world was
exploiting cotton business from South Asia and SAARC cotton
committee or association would protect the interests of its member
countries.
</P>
<P>
Mirani said the three members including Pakistan, India and
Bangladesh were producing cotton in the region and they should
exchange expertise amongst them.
</P>
<P>
This forum should exchange information and expertise in
technology, production, seed development and import and export to
benefit each other, said Mirani.
</P>
<P>
He said the western world was imposing uncalled barriers,
including anti-dumping, child labor clause on the exports from
developing countries, particularly from South Asia.
</P>
<P>
He believed that a cotton forum within SAARC is necessary and
practical to project the interests of the south Asian countries.
</P>
