<HEADLINE> 5 Trade Delegations to Visit Kuwait in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Five foreign delegations will
visit Kuwait in the next two weeks to find ways of promoting
cooperation in trade and investment, the Kuwaiti News Agency
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
An Irish delegation with representatives of 11 companies will
visit the Gulf sheikdom from Tuesday to Saturday within a trip to
the Gulf Cooperation Council states which also include Saudi
Arabia, Oman, the United Arab Emirates, Qatar and Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
A Brazilian delegation will be here in the same period.
</P>
<P>
A Russian delegation including representatives of 40 companies
and ministries will arrive here on Saturday for a week-long
visit. It will hold a seminar with Kuwaiti businessmen on
investment in Russia.
</P>
<P>
A Canadian delegation headed by an advisor to the Ministry of
Trade and Industry will arrive here on March 28, and a number of
Canadian companies will exhibit their products and services in the
country.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the month, a Bahraini delegation will also visit
Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Commercial Department of the U.S. embassy in
Kuwait will display brochures for more than 250 U.S. companies on
March 29-30. 
