<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola: Ex-Chief Expelled from Opposition Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA) said on Monday that its former
General Secretary Eugenio Manuvakola has been expelled.
</P>
<P>
The opposition party announced this in its headquarters in the
central city of Ballundo.
</P>
<P>
According to the official Angolan News Agency, UNITA issued a
news release, saying that the decision of expelling Manuvakola
was made by its Political Commission last weekend. It said that
the Political Commission decided to expel the former general
secretary because he has violated the party constitution.
</P>
<P>
The commission said in its announcement that as of that day,
Manuvakola would not be a member of UNITA any more and he should
be responsible for himself. He can no longer speak for UNITA and
his speeches and political activities will have nothing to do
with the party.
</P>
<P>
Manuvakola has been one of the senior leaders of UNITA. He
entered the Central Committee in 1975 and became one of the
Politburo members in November 1988. He was elected as the General
Secretary of UNITA in 1992.
</P>
<P>
UNITA expelled Manuvakola largely because of his critical
speech against the party leaders on the official radio last
Friday, in which he said that UNITA was already incapable of
waging a war against the government and expressed his hope that
UNITA members should give up their idea of doing that and isolate
its President Jonas Savimbi.
</P>
<P>
Manuvakola also said that except a peaceful solution, there is
no way out and Savimbi should be aware of this and discard his
absurd attitude toward the peace process. Savimbi always plans to
find a military solution instead of a peaceful one.
</P>
<P>
In November 1994, Manuvakola, representing UNITA, signed a
peaceful agreement with the Angolan government in Lusaka, the
capital city of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Because of his dispute with the leaders of UNITA on the peace
process, Manuvakola was discharged from the position of the
General Secretary.
</P>
<P>
Manuvakola fled Ballundo where he had been jailed and arrived
in Luanda in November 1997, and after that he still regarded
himself a member of UNITA and declared that "without Savimbi,
UNITA will exist just the same." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
