<HEADLINE> 48,000 Russian Officers Face Dismissal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Some 48,000 Russian officers will
be laid off before the end of the year due to a merger of the
military air defense troops, Col. Gen. Anatoly Kornukov, the
military air force commander-in-chief, said Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Interfax news agency, Kornukov, who is
currently inspecting the Zabaikalye Military District, said that
about 125,000 servicemen and 39 generals will be laid off from the
military air force and the air defense troops this year.
</P>
<P>
However, the cuts will in no way afflict the combat readiness
of the military air force or Russia's security, the general said.
Aircraft and equipment in the military air force and the air
defense troops will undergo necessary repairs, he was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
In his view, the military potential will rise due to quality
rather than quantity.
</P>
<P>
Kornukov said the military air force will not receive new
equipment until the year 2001. 
</P>
</TEXT>
