<HEADLINE> 13 Killed in Traffic Accidents in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen people were killed in
three traffic accidents in Turkey on Monday, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
A Turkish minibus flew into a water channel near Gocu village
of Karatay town in Konya, central Anatolia, Monday afternoon,
killing seven people.
</P>
<P>
Three Turks were killed, four injured and three others are
still missing when another passenger minibus ran into a water
channel in Antalya province near the Mediterranean Sea Monday
morning, added the news agency.
</P>
<P>
Three people were killed after a truck turned over near Aksu
village of Tortum town in Erzurum province.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents increased Monday due to snow fall in various
regions of Turkey, according to the agency. 
</P>
