<HEADLINE> Security Council Decides to lift Restrictions of Sale, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the resolution, the Council welcomed the return to Sierra
Leone of its democratically elected President in March 10, 1998.
</P>
<P>
It also welcomed the intention of U.N. Secretary-General to
make proposals concerning the role of the United Nations and its
future presence in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The Council decided to review the other prohibitions on
Sierra Leone in the light of developments and further discussion
with the Government of Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
A coup took place in Sierra Leone last May which overthrew the
democratically elected Government. The junta was forced to step
down by the peacekeeping troops from the the Western African
nations last month. With the help of the international community,
the democratically elected president returned to Sierra Leone on
March 10.  
</P>
</TEXT>
