<HEADLINE> Security Council Authorizes MISAB to Extend its Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the resolution, the Security Council welcomed the efforts
made by the member states participating in MISAB and by those
states providing support to them, and their readiness to
maintain these efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Council urged the parties in the Central African
Republic to complete the implementation of the provisions of
te Bangui Agreement and to implement the conclusions of the
National Reconciliation Conference.
</P>
<P>
The Council encouraged member States of MISAB to contribute
to the Trust Fund for the Central African Republic.
</P>
<P>
It affirmed that it will take a decision by March 27, 1998, on
the establishment of a United Nations peacekeeping operation in
the Central African Republic on the basis of the U.N.
Secretary-General's report.  
</P>
</TEXT>
